                 illumination functions were represented by real
                 spectral energy distribution on a wavelength basis,
                 rather than arbitary RGB colour triplets. Cook also
                 applied the Fresnel equation for reflection, resulting
                 in more accurate specular highlight intensities and
                 colour for metallic surfaces. This model is applicable
                 to a broad range of materials, surface conditions, and
                 lighting situations. - Vignasekaran 4/94",
