  abstract =     "In this report we propose a new model to represent
                 spectral functions called the composite model. This
                 model is built on the idea that we decompose all
                 spectral functions into smooth and spiky components,
                 each with its own distinct representation.
                 Specifically, a smooth spectrum can be expressed as a
                 linear combination of a set of given basis functions
                 and thus be represented through the corresponding
                 coefficients. The discrete spikes in a spiky spectral
