                 locations and heights. For the smooth spectra, we
                 propose re-sampling the functions that are
                 reconstructed from the coefficients in the linear
                 combination to improve efficiency. Spectral
                 multiplications are thus greatly reduced in complexity.
                 This new model demonstrates remarkable advantages in
                 representing spectral functions with aspect to
                 accuracy, compactness, computational efficiency,
                 portability, and flexibility. We expect that this work
